sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K199054
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This design is projected to exhibit XOR logic. The inputs are high osmolarity and 3OC6.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kin Lau

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFPr
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The mRFP coding sequence in the reverse orientation. This part requires a reverse RBS and reverse promoter to be expressed
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Karmella Haynes
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: RFP reverse was PCR amplified from mRFP (BBaE1010).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: RFP reverse was PCR amplified from mRFP (BBaE1010) using the following primers: 5'-atgcactagtatggcttcctccgaagacgt "Spe mRFP F" 5'-gcattctagattaagcaccggtggagtgac "Xba mRFP R"

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J44001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Todd Eckdahl
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Repeats in oligos caused unusual products during cloning

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K199017
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: pOmpC is the promoter upstream of the OmpC gene which is native to E. coli. pOmpC is induced by high osmolarity, such as LB media and high sucrose concentration.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kin Lau
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: PCR was used to isolate the promoter and add BioBrick ends to it.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K199052
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is pLux oriented in an opposite direction to typical BioBrick inserts.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kin Lau
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Had trouble getting this part via PCR. That was probably due to an error in the primers.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Weak1 RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-2" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: GFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: green fluorescent protein derived from jellyfish Aequeora victoria wild-type GFP (SwissProt: P42212
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: GFP (mut3b) [note that this part does not have a barcode]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: jcbraff

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
